
[1]invert

   INVERT', v.t. [L.inverto; in and verto, to turn.]

   1. To turn into a contrary direction; to turn upside down; as, to
   invert a cone; to invert a hollow vessel.

   2. To place in a contrary order or method; as, to invert the rules of
   justice; to invert the order of words.

   And winter storms invert the year.

   3. In music, to change the order of the notes which form a chord, or
   the parts which compose harmony.

   4. To divert; to turn into another channel; to embezzle. [Not in use.]
